Spectral Doppler flow profiles in neonates with obstructive lesions of the aortic arch. The aim was to assess the value of continuous and pulsed wave Doppler ultrasound in the detection and differentiation of obstructive lesions of the aortic arch in neonates. In 31 neonates with proven arch obstruction (pre- or juxtaductal coarctation in 19 patients postductal coarctation in five patients